{
  "local_port": 35774,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I cook manchurian?",
  "response": "Manchurian is a popular Indo-Chinese dish typically made with either vegetable, chicken, or paneer balls that are deep-fried and then tossed in a flavorful sauce. Here's a basic recipe for making Vegetable Manchurian:\n\n### Ingredients\n\n**For the Manchurian Balls:**\n- 1 cup finely chopped mixed vegetables (cabbage, carrots, bell peppers, beans, etc.)\n- 1/4 cup finely chopped onions\n- 2-3 tablespoons all-purpose flour (maida)\n- 2-3 tablespoons cornflour (cornstarch)\n- 1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\n- Salt to taste\n- Black pepper to taste\n- 1/2 teaspoon soy sauce (optional)\n- Oil for deep frying\n\n**For the Manchurian Sauce:**\n- 2 tablespoons oil\n- 3-4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1-inch piece ginger, minced\n- 1-2 green chilies, finely chopped (adjust to taste)\n- 1/4 cup finely chopped onions\n- 1/4 cup bell peppers, chopped (optional)\n- 2-3 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 1-2 tablespoons chili sauce (adjust to taste)\n- 1 tablespoon tomato ketchup\n- 1 teaspoon vinegar (optional)\n- 1/2 cup water (adjust for desired consistency)\n- Salt to taste\n- Green onions, chopped for garnish\n\n### Instructions\n\n#### Prepare the Manchurian Balls:\n1. **Mix Ingredients:** In a mixing bowl, combine the chopped vegetables, onions, all-purpose flour, cornflour, ginger-garlic paste, soy sauce, salt, and black pepper. Mix well until the mixture is combined and slightly sticky.\n  \n2. **Form Balls:** Take small portions of the mixture and shape them into small balls (about 1 inch in diameter).\n\n3. **Fry the Balls:** Heat oil in a deep frying pan or wok over medium heat. Once hot, carefully add the balls in batches and fry until they are golden brown and cooked through. Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.\n\n#### Prepare the Sauce:\n1. **Heat Oil:** In another pan or wok, heat 2 tablespoons of oil over medium-high heat.\n\n2. **Saut\u00e9:** Add minced garlic, ginger, and chopped green chilies. Saut\u00e9 for a few seconds until aromatic.\n\n3. **Add Onions and Peppers:** Add the chopped onions and bell peppers (if using) and saut\u00e9 until they become translucent.\n\n4. **Add Sauces:** Mix in the soy sauce, chili sauce, tomato ketchup, and vinegar. Stir well.\n\n5. **Add Water:** Pour in the water and bring to a simmer. Adjust the thickness of the sauce by adding more water or letting it cook longer to reduce.\n\n6. **Combine:** Add the fried Manchurian balls to the sauce and toss gently to coat them in the sauce. Cook for a couple of minutes so they absorb the flavors.\n\n7. **Garnish:** Garnish with chopped green onions.\n\n### Serve\nServe the Manchurian hot with steamed rice or noodles as a main dish or as an appetizer with toothpicks.\n\nEnjoy your delicious homemade Vegetable Manchurian!",
